The foundation stone for Karnataka Regional Engineering College (KREC) was laid on 6 August 1960,[3]¬†at¬†Surathkal. It was made possible through the efforts of¬†U. Srinivas Mallya¬†and¬†V. S. Kudva¬†and the area is now called Srinivasnagar in his honour. KREC began with three under-graduate courses in engineering:¬†Mechanical,¬†Electrical, and¬†Civil, with affiliation to the¬†University of Mysore. 1965 saw the beginning of under-graduate courses in¬†Chemical¬†and¬†Metallurgical Engineering. In 1966, the college started its first postgraduate course in Marine Structures and Industrial Structures, followed by post-graduate courses in Industrial Electronics (1969), Heat Power (1971), Hydraulics and Water Resources (1971), Chemical Plant Design Engineering (1971) and Process Metallurgy (1972).  More under-graduate engineering courses were added later:¬†Electronics and Communication Engineering¬†(1971),¬†Mining Engineering¬†(1984),¬†Computer Engineering¬†(1986) and information technology (2000). In 1980, KREC came under the affiliation of¬†Mangalore University, and the five-year under-graduate courses were shortened to four-years. On 26 June 2002, it was elevated to the status of a¬†National Institute of Technology¬†and has been called NIT Karnataka (NITK) ever since. It is now a¬†Deemed University. NITK celebrated its 50th Institute Foundation day on 6 August 2009. The year-long Golden Jubilee celebrations were inaugurated on 10 August 2009

It was founded in 1960 as KREC while today, it is one of the 32¬†National Institutes of Technology¬†in India and is recognised as an¬†Institute of National Importance¬†by the¬†Government of India. It has a suburban campus, in close proximity to the¬†Arabian Sea. National Highway 66 runs through the campus and serves as the major mode of access.

Located in a picturesque location close to the Western Ghats, this is one of the premier institutes in India for Engineering. Complete with a lot of amenities like basketball court, swimming pool, tennis and football courts and multiple food joints, this place is any engineering student's dream. Although located on a highway, public transport to this place is extremely frequent from cities like Mangalore (30 mins travel) or Manipal(1hour travel). There are quite a view scenic places of interest and a multitude of food joints in the close vicinity of this place too. The USP of this place is that it has a private beach accessible only to residents of the campus, although this entrance has timings.

Who doesn't like college life, what if it is very close to a beach, can't imagine right, exactly, NITK is one of the few colleges in the world, if I may say so,  very close to sea and has a private beach in its name.  I am a former student of NITK, batch of 2013 and I am proud to say that I am NITKian, cause my college life in NITK completely changed me. If there is anybody who would like to experience a thrilling college life, this is the college you should opt to. As you know, this is one of the top technical institutes in India.  It is well maintained with lot of greenery and managed by good management.  This is the place for nerdy people and party people and people who doesn't belong to neither groups. Has well built buildings, well equipped labs and good faculty. NITK is about 20 KM far from Mangalore city, so if you're searching for a place to hangout, it's not too far. Even though hostel was very good, the hostel food was not upto the mark. So, you might want to save your pocket money, because there are plenty of places to eat food, inside the campus and outside of it. When it comes to teaching facility, it has a good library and private study rooms and free computer center. College has two big playing grounds, indoor stadium for table tennis and badminton, separate court for basketball, volleyball and tennis. And, there is a big, well maintained swimming pool.  So, what else you need, get ready to crack the entrance exam and join this fantastic, marvelous college.

Amazing place to grow. You get a lot of exposure to each kind of domain whether it may be related to academics or other extra curricular activities. Infrastructure is fantastic with state of the art labs(take any department),computer labs, comfortable hostels and sports arena. Placements are really exceptional and fantastic with IT-firms rushing into the college to grab best talents at the earliest and if you are in circuit or core branches then a good healthy job is almost guaranteed. The college is filled with lots of fun and excitement in association with free environment to work and bloom. The Technical and cultural fests are really awesome,one of the biggest in South Asia. Last but not the least the Beach is very pleasant and it's the only college to have its own private beach. So overall if you are enthusiastic and ready to put efforts, this is a very good place to be.
